Real Solutions PH Template License
==================================

This repository combines two layers of code under different terms:

  1. The original upstream template ("Upstream Code") by Sebastián Ramírez,
     distributed under the MIT License (reproduced below).
  2. All modifications, additions, configurations, integrations, and original
     works contributed to this repository by Real Solutions PH ("Template
     Code"), which are proprietary to Real Solutions PH and governed by the
     terms in Section A below.

Downstream projects derived from this repository ("Client Projects") will
typically contain a third layer ("Client Code") whose ownership is determined
by the written services agreement between Real Solutions PH and the client.
Section B below describes the default position absent a conflicting agreement.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION A — Template Code (Real Solutions PH Proprietary)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Copyright (c) 2026 Real Solutions PH. All rights reserved.

"Template Code" means every file, line, asset, configuration, script, schema,
and documentation contributed to this repository by Real Solutions PH or its
personnel, including any future versions thereof, but excluding the Upstream
Code identified in Section C.

1. Ownership. Real Solutions PH retains all right, title, and interest in and
   to the Template Code, including all copyright and other intellectual
   property rights, in perpetuity. No transfer or assignment of ownership in
   the Template Code occurs by virtue of this repository being used to start,
   build, deliver, host, or operate any Client Project, regardless of whether
   that Client Project is, or later becomes, deployed, distributed,
   commercialized, or otherwise made publicly available.

2. Internal Reuse. Real Solutions PH may use, copy, modify, extend, sublicense
   (as part of Client Projects), and incorporate the Template Code into any
   number of present or future projects, products, or engagements, including
   projects undertaken concurrently with, after, or for clients other than the
   client of any earlier engagement that used the Template Code. Use of the
   Template Code in one Client Project does not exhaust, restrict, or
   encumber Real Solutions PH's right to use the same Template Code in any
   other Client Project.

3. Client Use. Clients of Real Solutions PH receive a non-exclusive,
   non-transferable, royalty-free license to use the Template Code solely as
   integrated into the specific Client Project delivered to them, for the
   internal and commercial operation of that Client Project. Clients do not
   acquire ownership of the Template Code, may not extract the Template Code
   for use in unrelated projects, and may not redistribute the Template Code
   as a standalone template, framework, or starter kit.

4. No Third-Party Distribution. Except as expressly permitted in Section A.3,
   the Template Code may not be copied, sublicensed, sold, published, or
   distributed by any party other than Real Solutions PH without Real
   Solutions PH's prior written consent.

5. Warranty Disclaimer. The Template Code is provided "AS IS", without
   warranty of any kind, express or implied, including but not limited to the
   warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and
   non-infringement. In no event shall Real Solutions PH be liable for any
   claim, damages, or other liability arising from, out of, or in connection
   with the Template Code or its use.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION B — Client Code (Default Position)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

"Client Code" means modules, business logic, features, integrations, content,
designs, and any other code or assets built on top of the Template Code
specifically for a particular client engagement, that are not part of the
Template Code or Upstream Code.

Absent a written agreement to the contrary between Real Solutions PH and the
client, Client Code authored by Real Solutions PH in the course of delivering a
Client Project is assigned to the client upon full payment of the agreed fees
for that engagement, on a work-for-hire basis to the maximum extent permitted
by applicable law. The client's ownership of Client Code does not extend to,
and is expressly carved out from, the Template Code and the Upstream Code,
which remain governed by Sections A and C respectively.

This Section B is descriptive of Real Solutions PH's default contracting
position. The operative ownership of Client Code in any given engagement is
governed by the executed services agreement for that engagement, which
controls in the event of any conflict with this section.

